Usage: quill cover [flags] [<template-name>]

Renders one template (-data + name) or a JSON list of cases (-cases),
collects template coverage, and writes a text/lcov/html report.

Flags:
  -autoescape string
    	output escaping strategy: "off" (default) or "html" (default "off")
  -cases string
    	JSON file of {template,data} cases; unions coverage across all
  -data string
    	JSON data file for a single-template run ("-" reads stdin)
  -fail-under float
    	exit non-zero if total unit coverage percent is below N
  -format string
    	report format: text (default), lcov, or html (default "text")
  -o string
    	output file for the report (default stdout)
  -root string
    	template root the loader resolves names under (default ".")
  -strict
    	strict-undefined handling; -strict=false enables lenient mode (default true)
  -threshold float
    	alias for -fail-under
